Name: USDA_Class
Description: Used by USDA to deliver their bale classing information. Documentation: https://www.ams.usda.gov/sites/default/files/media/Cotton%20DB%20Understanding%20the%20Data.pdf

Fields.Name: Gin Code Number
Fields.Description: first two digits denotes Classing Office, last three digits identify the gin

Fields.Name: Gin Bale Number
Fields.Description: bar-coded bale ID tag, printed with gin code number and gin bale number

Fields.Name: Bales in Module/Trailer
Fields.Description: Number of bales in the module/trailer  with the module average calculation.

Fields.Name: Official Color Grade
Fields.Description: Upland color grade for classification is determined by instrument measurements. Pima color grade for classification is determined by human classer.

Fields.Name: Strength
Fields.Description: Force in grams required to break a bundle of fibers one tex unit in size.

Fields.Name: Leaf Grade
Fields.Description: Cotton plant leaf remaining in the lint after the ginning process.

Fields.Name: Extraneous Matter
Fields.Description: Substance in the cotton other than fiber or leaf.

Fields.Name: Remarks
Fields.Description: Special conditions that may cause processing problems and lower yarn quality.

Fields.Name: Instrument ColorCode
Fields.Description: Official color grade for Upland cotton. Two digits are shown on the classification for Pima cotton

Fields.Name: Color Quadrant
Fields.Description: color grade is subdivided to denote differences within a color grade

Fields.Name: Color +b
Fields.Description: Determination of how much yellow color is in the sample.

Fields.Name: Non-Lint Content (Trash Percent Area)
Fields.Description: Trash particles as determined by image analysis.

Fields.Name: Length Uniformity Index (Percent)
Fields.Description: Degree of uniformity of the fibers in a sample .

Fields.Name: Upland or Pima
Fields.Description: One-digit code indicates whether the sample is Upland or American Pima.

Fields.Name: Record Type
Fields.Description: One-digit code indicates the type of record.

Fields.Name: Record Status
Fields.Description: Indicates whether or not the manual classing information has been corrected.

Fields.Name: CCC Loan Premiums and Discounts
Fields.Description: CCC loan premium and discount points for Upland cotton.  Loan price for Pima cotton is  cents per pound.

Name: Deere_HID
Description: Harvest ID file (HID); created by John Deere harvesters

Fields.Name: GmtDate
Fields.zzComment: problem with Nustache; when read as Date a field can't be accessed using Nustache

Name: FSA_Trailer
Description:
FSA Cotton Data File Format - Trailer
Documentation: USDA FSA Handbook 7-CN (http://www.fsa.usda.gov/FSA/webapp?area=home&subject=empl&topic=hbk), Exhibit 13

Fields.Name: State Code
Fields.Description: State where the loan or LDP will be made

Fields.Name: County Code
Fields.Description: Code for the county where the loan or LDP will be made.

Fields.Name: Record Count
Fields.Description: Number of bales on the loan or LDP.

Name: FSA_Header
Description:
FSA Cotton Data File Format - Header
Documentation: USDA FSA Handbook 7-CN (http://www.fsa.usda.gov/FSA/webapp?area=home&subject=empl&topic=hbk), Exhibit 13

Fields.Name: State Code
Fields.Description: State where the loan or LDP will be made

Fields.Name: County Code
Fields.Description: County where the loan or LDP will be made.

Fields.Name: Commodity Code
Fields.Description: Commodity code, “UP” for upland or “ELS” for extra long staple.

Fields.Name: Warehouse Code
Fields.Description: LDP’s not based on warehouse receipts, enter “999999” as the warehouse code.

Fields.Name: Producer Fee
Fields.Description: Amount of producer fee (No Decimal) if applicable.

Fields.Name: Receiving Charges
Fields.Description: If prepaid, enter “Y”, if not, enter "N".

Name: FSA_Detail
Description:
FSA Cotton Data File Format - Detail
Documentation: USDA FSA Handbook 7-CN (http://www.fsa.usda.gov/FSA/webapp?area=home&subject=empl&topic=hbk), Exhibit 13

Fields.Name: State Code
Fields.Description: Code for the State where the loan or LDP will be made.

Fields.Name: County Code
Fields.Description: Code for the County where the loan or LDP will be made.

Fields.Name: File Sequence Number
Fields.Description: Number  begins with last digit of crop year and number 0001. Crop year and increases by 1 for each file

Fields.Name: Warehouse Receipt Number
Fields.Description: Warehouse receipt number for the bale

Fields.Name: Class Date
Fields.Description: Date bale was classed. Enter in MMDDYY format.

Fields.Name: Receipt Date
Fields.Description: Date receipt was issued. Enter MMDDYY format.

Fields.Name: Storage Date
Fields.Description: Storage start date. Enter in MMDDYY format.

Fields.Name: Warehouse Code
Fields.Description: Warehouse Code that identifies the storage location

junk.Note: we key off of the '20' in the crop year to keep from getting confused with a type 83 detail

Fields.Name: Up To Date
Fields.Description: Totals calculated as of date; MMDDYYYY

Fields.Name: Up To Time
Fields.Description: Totals calculated as of time; HHMMSS

Fields.Name: Current Holder Balance
Fields.Description: Total number of receipts held as of 12:00 midnight of the previous day (this total does not include canceled receipts)

Fields.Name: Subholder Balance (no CCC or Whse)
Fields.Description: Total number of receipts held as subholder - This total excludes receipts held by warehouses and CCC

Fields.Name: Subholder Balance (CCC is Holder)
Fields.Description: Total number of receipts in Price Support Loan Program (CCC is Holder) and recipient of acknowledgment/summary is the Subholder

Fields.Name: Electronic Receipts held (Whse Only)
Fields.Description: Total number of uncanceled Electronic Receipts held (Received by warehouses only)

Fields.Name: Paper Receipts Held (Whse Only)
Fields.Description: Total number of uncanceled Paper Receipts held (Received by warehouses only)

Fields.Name: Under Shipping Order
Fields.Description: Total number of receipts under a shipping order

Fields.Name: Pending Bank
Fields.Description: Total number of receipts pending a bank release

Name: EWR_HD_Header
Description: Describes bales in detail; Short record omits grade fields

Fields.Name: Request Field/Activity Field
Fields.Description: Text comment regarding the batch  or properties based on field 4.

Fields.Name: Holder Selection
Fields.Description: Empty unless batch type 65 Then the following rules applie

Fields.Name: Draft Number
Fields.Description: Bank Draft Number - if delivered via bank draft, otherwise zero or empty

Fields.Name: Draft Amount
Fields.Description: Draft Amount - if delivered via bank draft, otherwise zero or empty

Fields.Name: Long/Short Record
Fields.Description: N = Short Record (no classing data) default; Y = Long Record (with classing data)

Fields.Name: Holder Type
Fields.Description: Output of holder selection type; i.e., Holder; Subholder; Both. This is only filled on batch types 65 and 60

Fields.Name: Issue Date
Fields.Description: Date entered by the warehouse, not assigned by EWR – Storage date of the bale – MMDDYYYY

Fields.Name: Tare Weight
Fields.Description: Represents pounds subtracted from gross weight to compensate for bagging and ties on the bale

Fields.Name: Net Weight
Fields.Description: Gross weight of bale minus tare weight – User enters appropriate amount

Fields.Name: Storage Fee
Fields.Description: If Storage Charge Frequency is Daily, the entry will display as cents/day

Fields.Name: Receiving Paid
Fields.Description: Y=receiving paid or waived N = not paid or waived

Fields.Name: Loading Paid
Fields.Description: Y= Paid; N=Not paid or waived

Fields.Name: Reconcentrated
Fields.Description: R = Bale is reconcentrated Space = Not reconcentrated

Fields.Name: Previous Warehouse
Fields.Description: Code of previous warehouse - Entered only if the bale is reconcentrated

Fields.Name: Previous Receipt Number
Fields.Description: Warehouse receipt number from previous warehouse, entered for reconcentrated cotton only

Fields.Name: Gin Tag Number
Fields.Description: Sequential tag number assigned by the gin

Fields.Name: Storage Paid Through

Fields.Description: Farm Serial number used for identifying specific areas of production

Fields.Name: CCC Loan Type
Fields.Description: A = Form A; G = Form G; Blank = no loan

Fields.Name: CCC Loan Date
Fields.Description: This field is initially supplied by the sender of the loan batch. Later it is updated by CCC when the loan is accepted, rejected or updated by CCC.

Fields.Name: Mark
Fields.Description: f the receipt is under shipment, then this field is the shipper mark. Otherwise it is the mark from the batch header upload

Fields.Name: Purchase Order Number
Fields.Description: Purchase Order Number assigned by seller

Fields.Name: Current Holder Type
Fields.Description: M = Merchant W = Warehouse G = Gin Z = Coop P = Producer C = Government B = Bank

Fields.Name: Loan Transfer
Fields.Description: Y = Yes. This bale was transferred while under loan

Fields.Name: Is Stored Outside
Fields.Description: Y=Yes Issue Date is date moved outside; N=No, Bale is inside; Blank=unknown

Fields.Name: EWR Definition ID
Fields.Description: Reference to the EWR Definition for a cotton receipt
